ure\u0219 (river)|Maros]] river embankment near [[Mak\u00f3]], [[\u00d3pusztaszer National Heritage Park]], and [[Szeged Cathedral|Cathedral of Szeged]]}}\n| image_flag              = FLAG-Csongrad-megye.svg\n| image_shield            = HU Csongr\u00e1d megye COA.svg\n| image_map               = HU county Csongrad.svg\n| map_alt                 = \n| map_caption             = Csongr\u00e1d County within Hungary\n| subdivision_type        = [[List of sovereign states|Country]]\n| subdivision_name        = {{HUN}}\n| subdivision_type1       = [[Regions of Hungary|Region]]\n| subdivision_name1       = [[Southern Great Plain]]\n| seat_type               = County seat\n| seat                    = [[Szeged]]\n| parts_type              = [[Districts of Hungary|Districts]]\n| parts                   = 7 districts\n| p1 = [[Csongr\u00e1d District]]\n| p2 = {{nowrap|[[H\u00f3dmez\u0151v\u00e1s\u00e1rhely District]]}}\n| p3 = [[Kistelek District]]\n| p4 = [[Mak\u00f3 District]]\n| p5 = [[M\u00f3rahalom District]]\n| p6 = [[Szeged District]]\n| p7 = [[Szentes District]]\n| government_footnotes    = \n| leader_title \t          = President of the General Assembly\n| leader_name \t          = B\u00e9la Kakas\n| leader_party            = [[Fidesz]]-[[Christian Democratic People's Party (Hungary)|KDNP]]\n| area_total_km2          = 4262.71\n| area_rank               = [[Counties of Hungary|12th in Hungary]]\n| population_as_of        = 2015\n| population_total        = 406205<ref>[http://nepesseg.com/csongrad/ nepesseg.com, population data of Hungarians settlements]</ref>\n| population_rank         = [[Counties of Hungary|8th in Hungary]]\n| population_density_km2  = auto\n| postal_code_type        = [[Postal codes in Hungary|Postal code]]\n| postal_code             = 66xx \u2013 69xx\n| area_code_type          = [[Telephone numbers in Hungary|Area code(s)]]\n| area_code               = (+36) 62, 63\n| iso_code                = {{mono|HU-CS}}\n|website                 = {{URL|http://www.csongrad-megye.hu/}}\n}}\n'''Csongr\u00e1d''' ({{lang-hu|Csongr\u00e1d megye}} {{IPA-hu|\u02c8t\u0361\u0283o\u014b\u0261ra\u02d0d|}}), set to be renamed '''Csongr\u00e1d-Csan\u00e1d''' from 2020<ref>[https://www.delmagyar.hu/szeged_hirek/csongrad-csanad_lesz_a_megye_neve_2020-tol/2534751/ Csongr\u00e1d-Csan\u00e1d lesz a megye neve 2020-t\u00f3l]</ref> is the name of an administrative county ([[Counties of Hungary|comitatus]] or ''megye'') in southern [[Hungary]], straddling the river [[Tisza]], on the border with [[Serbia]] and [[Romania]]. It shares borders with the Hungarian counties [[B\u00e1cs-Kiskun]], [[J\u00e1sz-Nagykun-Szolnok]] and [[B\u00e9k\u00e9s (county)|B\u00e9k\u00e9s]]. The administrative centre of Csongr\u00e1d county is [[Szeged]]. The county is also part of the [[Danube-Kris-Mures-Tisa]] euroregion.\n\n==History==\nOn October 3, 2017, the Hungarian Parliament passed a resolution to rename Csongr\u00e1d County to Csongr\u00e1d-Csan\u00e1d, which will take effect on June 4, 2020.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://vasarhelyilokalpatriotak.blog.hu/2017/10/04/csongrad_csanad_megye_az_uj_elnevezes|title=Csongr\u00e1d - Csan\u00e1d megye, az \u00faj elnevez\u00e9s v\u00e9delm\u00e9ben|last=Harmat \u00c1rp\u00e1d|first=P\u00e9ter|date=October 5, 2017|website=|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=April 4, 2020}}</ref> The resolution was submitted by J\u00e1nos L\u00e1z\u00e1r, then-Minister of the Prime Minister's Office, who called the renaming symbolic as more than a dozen settlements in the area still share Csan\u00e1d County's identity.<ref>{{Cite news|last=|first=|url=https://hvg.hu/itthon/20171003_uj_neve_van_csongrad_megyenek|title=\u00daj neve van Csongr\u00e1d megy\u00e9nek|date=October 3, 2017|work=HVG|access-date=April 07, 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n==Geography==\nThis county has a total area of {{convert|4263|sqkm|sqmi|0|abbr=on}} \u2013 4,58% of Hungary.\n\nThe area of Csongr\u00e1d County is flat. It has a high number of sunshine hours and excellent soil, which makes it the most important agricultural area of Hungary. Its most famous products are [[paprika]] from [[Szeged]] and [[onion|onions]] from [[Mak\u00f3]], but grain, vegetables, and fruits are also significant. Half of the onions, paprika, and vegetables produced in Hungary are from Csongr\u00e1d. The county is also rich in oil and natural gas.\n\nThe highest point is \u00c1sotthalom (125 m), the lowest is Gy\u00e1lar\u00e9t (78 m; lowest point of Hungary).\n\n===Neighbours===\n* [[J\u00e1sz-Nagykun-Szolnok County]] in the North.\n* [[B\u00e9k\u00e9s County]] in the East.\n* {{ROU}} and {{SRB}} in the South \u2013 [[Timi\u0219 County]] and [[North Ba\u010dka District]]\n* [[B\u00e1cs-Kiskun County]] in the West.\n\n==Demographics==\n{{Pie chart\n|thumb = right\n|caption = Religion in Csongr\u00e1d County (2011 census)\n|label1 = [[Catholic Church]]\n|value1 = 39.4\n|color1 = DarkOrchid\n|label2 = [[Greek Catholicism]]\n|value2 = 0.4\n|color2 = MediumOrchid\n|label3 = [[Calvinism]]\n|value3 = 7.0\n|color3 = DodgerBlue\n|label4 = [[Lutheranism]]\n|value4 = 0.8\n|color4 = DeepSkyBlue\n|label5 = [[Orthodoxy]]\n|value5 = 0.2\n|color5 = FireBrick\n|label6 = [[Judaism]]\n|value6 = 0.1\n|color6 = Orange\n|label7 = Other religions\n|value7 = 1.7\n|color7 = Chartreuse\n|label8 = [[Irreligion|Non-religious]]\n|value8 = 21.8\n|color8 = Honeydew\n|label9 = [[Atheism|Atheists]]\n|value9 = 1.6\n|color9 = Grey\n|label10= Undeclared\n|value10= 27.0\n|color10= Black\n}}\n{{see also|Demographics of Hungary}}\nAfter the end of the [[Ottoman Hungary|Ottoman occupation]] in 1715, the county was nearly uninhabited, with a [[population density]] of less than 5/km<sup>2</sup>. In the 18th and 19th centuries, the county was repopulated by ethnic [[Hungarians]] from the relatively overpopulated northern and western counties of the [[Kingdom of Hungary]].<ref>Changing ethnicities in Hungary (map+data+assay) (K\u00e1roly Kocsis, Zsolt Bottlik, [[Magyar Tudom\u00e1nyos Akad\u00e9mia|MTA]] F\u00f6ldrajztudom\u00e1nyi Kutat\u00f3int\u00e9zet, [[Budapest]] 2009, {{ISBN|978-963-9545-18-2}}, {{ISBN|978-963-9545-19-9}})</ref> According to the 2001 census, the county is home for 423,826 people (216,936 people live in [[counties of Hungary|urban counties]]) with a population density is 100/km<sup>2</sup>. It has a [[Hungarian people|Hungarian]] majority.<ref>[http://www.nepszamlalas.hu/eng/volumes/06/06/tabeng/toc1.html Csongr\u00e1d county (2001 census), English]</ref>\n\nIn 2015, it had a population of 406,205 and the [[population density]] was 95/km\u00b2.\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n! Year\n! County population<ref>n\u00e9pess\u00e9g.com, ''[http://nepesseg.com/csongrad/ \"Csongr\u00e1d megye n\u00e9pess\u00e9ge 1870-2015\"]''</ref>\n! Change\n|-\n| 1949\n| 429,083\n|align=\"right\"| n/a\n|-\n| 1960\n|{{increase}} 434,046\n|align=\"right\"| 1.16%\n|-\n| 1970\n|{{increase}} 445,220\n|align=\"right\"| 2.57%\n|-\n| 1980\n|{{increase}} 456,300 (record)\n|align=\"right\"| 2.49%\n|-\n| 1990\n|{{decrease}} 438,842\n|align=\"right\"| -3.83%\n|-\n| 2001\n|{{decrease}} 433,344\n|align=\"right\"| -1.25%\n|-\n| 2011\n|{{decrease}} 417,456\n|align=\"right\"| -3.67%\n|}\n\n===Ethnicity===\nBesides the Hungarian majority, the main minorities are the Roma (approx. 5,000), Romanian (1,500), German (1,300) and Serb (1,300).\n\nTotal population (2011 census): 417,456<br />\nEthnic groups (2011 census):<ref>[http://www.ksh.hu/nepszamlalas/tablak_teruleti_06 1.1.6. A n\u00e9pess\u00e9g anyanyelv, nemzetis\u00e9g \u00e9s nemek szerint \u2013 Friss\u00edtve: 2013.04.17.; Hungarian Central Statistical Office] {{in lang|hu}}</ref>\nIdentified themselves: 367,193 persons:\n*[[Hungarians]]: 355,554 (96.83%)\n*[[Romani people in Hungary|Gypsies]]: 4,720 (1.29%)\n*Others and indefinable: 6,919 (1.88%)\n\nApproximately 59,000 persons in Csongr\u00e1d County did not declare their ethnic group on the 2011 census.\n\n===Religion===\n{{see also|Religion in Hungary}}\nReligious adherence in the county according to the 2011 census:<ref>2011. \u00c9VI N\u00c9PSZ\u00c1ML\u00c1L\u00c1S, 3. Ter\u00fcleti adatok, 3.6 Csongr\u00e1d megye, {{in lang|hu}} ''[http://www.terezvaros.hu/testuleti/nepsz2011-3/pdf/nepsz2011_03_06.pdf]''</ref>\n\n*Catholic \u2013 165,955 ([[Roman Catholicism in Hungary|Roman Catholic]] \u2013 164,060; [[Hungarian Greek Catholic Church|Greek Catholic]] \u2013 1,855);\n*[[Reformed Church in Hungary|Reformed]] \u2013 29,289; \n*[[Evangelical-Lutheran Church in Hungary|Evangelical]] \u2013 3,488;\n*[[Eastern Orthodoxy in Hungary|Orthodox]] \u2013 923;\n*[[History of the Jews in Hungary|Judaism]] \u2013 263;\n*Other religions \u2013 7,278; \n*[[Irreligion|Non-religious]] \u2013 90,836; \n*[[Atheism]] \u2013 6,585;\n*''Undeclared'' \u2013 112,839.\n\n==Regional structure==\n[[File:Csongr\u00e1d districts.png|thumb|right|350px|District of '''Csongr\u00e1d County''']]\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"font-size:95%\"\n|-bgcolor=\"D0D8DD\"\n| align=\"center\"|\u2116\n|style=width:175px; align=\"center\"|'''English''' and<br/>''Hungarian'' names\n| align=\"center\"|'''Area'''<br/> <small>(km\u00b2)</small>\n| align=\"center\"|'''Population'''<br/> <small>(2011)</small>\n| align=\"center\"|'''Density'''<br/> <small>(pop./km\u00b2)</small>\n| align=\"center\"|'''Seat'''\n| align=\"center\"|\u2116 of<br/>'''municipalities'''\n|-\n|align=\"center\"|1\n|[[Csongr\u00e1d District]]<br/> ''Csongr\u00e1di j\u00e1r\u00e1s''\n| align=\"right\"| 339.24\n|align=\"right\"| 22,996\n| align=\"right\"| 68\n|[[Csongr\u00e1d]] (town)\n| align=\"center\"|4\n|-\n|align=\"center\"|2\n|[[H\u00f3dmez\u0151v\u00e1s\u00e1rhely District]]<br/> ''H\u00f3dmez\u0151v\u00e1s\u00e1rhelyi j\u00e1r\u00e1s''\n| align=\"right\"| 707.77\n|align=\"right\"| 56,560\n| align=\"right\"| 80\n|[[H\u00f3dmez\u0151v\u00e1s\u00e1rhely]]\n| align=\"center\"|4\n|-\n|align=\"center\"|3\n|[[Kistelek District]]<br/> ''Kisteleki j\u00e1r\u00e1s''\n| align=\"right\"| 410.20\n|align=\"right\"| 18,185\n| align=\"right\"| 44\n|[[Kistelek]]\n| align=\"center\"|6\n|-\n|align=\"center\"|4\n|[[Mak\u00f3 District]]<br/> ''Mak\u00f3i j\u00e1r\u00e1s''\n| align=\"right\"| 688.85\n|align=\"right\"| 45,138\n| align=\"right\"| 66\n|[[Mak\u00f3]]\n| align=\"center\"|15\n|-\n|align=\"center\"|5\n|[[M\u00f3rahalom District]]<br/> ''M\u00f3rahalmi j\u00e1r\u00e1s''\n| align=\"right\"| 561.71\n|align=\"right\"| 28,986\n| align=\"right\"| 52\n|[[M\u00f3rahalom]]\n| align=\"center\"|10\n|-\n|align=\"center\"|6\n|[[Szeged District]]<br/> ''Szegedi j\u00e1r\u00e1s''\n| align=\"right\"| 741.10\n|align=\"right\"| 204,263\n| align=\"right\"| 276\n|[[Szeged]]\n| align=\"center\"|13\n|-\n|align=\"center\"|7\n|[[Szentes District]]<br/> ''Szentesi j\u00e1r\u00e1s''\n| align=\"right\"| 813.84\n|align=\"right\"| 41,328\n| align=\"right\"| 51\n|[[Szentes]]\n| align=\"center\"|8\n|-\n|-bgcolor=\"E5E4E2\"\n!colspan=\"2\"| Csongr\u00e1d County\n| align=\"right\"| '''4,262.71'''\n|align=\"right\"| '''417,456'''\n| align=\"right\"| '''98'''\n|'''[[Szeged]]'''\n| align=\"center\"|'''60'''\n|}\n\n== Transport ==\n\n=== Road network ===\n[[File:E75 Roszke.JPG|thumbnail|right|M5 motorway near R\u00f6szke.]]\n[[File:Szentes Attila \u00fat ker\u00e9kp\u00e1r\u00fat 2012-12-31.JPG|thumbnail|right|Main road 45 near Szentes.]]\n{{see also|Roads in Hungary|Highways in Hungary}}\nIn 2012, Csongr\u00e1d County has a dense network of public roads, in total length of 1,350&nbsp;km, of which 281&nbsp;km are main roads.<ref name=\"monografie\">{{cite journal |url=http://m.delmagyar.hu/delm/k02_munkaanyag.pdf |title=Csongr\u00e1d Megyei Ter\u00fclet fejleszt\u00e9si Koncepci\u00f3 |pages= |language=Hungarian}}</ref> Inland, connections are provided by 1,049&nbsp;km of county and communal roads and 20&nbsp;km are covered with light road surfaces.\n\n;Highway network\n*[[File:M5 (Hu) Otszogletu kek tabla.svg|30px|link=M5 motorway (Hungary)]] [[File:E75-HUN.svg|30px|link=European route E75]] runs from [[Budapest]] to [[R\u00f6szke]] ([[Serbia]]n border). ~ 47&nbsp;km \n*[[File:M9 (Hu) Otszogletu kek tabla.svg|30px|link=M9 expressway (Hungary)]] ''runs from [[Szombathely]] to [[Szeged]]. (planned)''\n*[[File:M43 (Hu) Otszogletu kek tabla.svg|30px|link=M43 motorway (Hungary)]] [[File:E68-HUN.svg|30px|link=European route E68]] runs from Szeged to [[Csan\u00e1dpalota]] ([[Romania]]n border). - 58&nbsp;km\n\n;Road network\n*[[File:5 (Hu) Otszogletu zold tabla.svg|25px]] runs from Budapest to R\u00f6szke (Serbian border), via [[Kistelek]] and Szeged. - 52&nbsp;km\n*[[File:43 (Hu) Otszogletu zold tabla.svg|25px]] runs from Szeged to [[Nagylak]], via [[Mak\u00f3]]. - 55&nbsp;km\n*430 runs from Mak\u00f3 to [[H\u00f3dmez\u0151v\u00e1s\u00e1rhely]]. - 30&nbsp;km\n*[[File:431 (Hu) Otszogletu zold tabla.svg|25px]] runs from Mak\u00f3 to [[Kiszombor]] (Romanian border). - 6&nbsp;km\n*[[File:45 (Hu) Otszogletu zold tabla.svg|25px]] runs from [[Kunszentm\u00e1rton]] to H\u00f3dmez\u0151v\u00e1s\u00e1rhely, via [[Szentes]]. - 43&nbsp;km\n*[[File:47 (Hu) Otszogletu zold tabla.svg|25px]] runs from Szeged to [[Debrecen]], via H\u00f3dmez\u0151v\u00e1s\u00e1rhely.\n*[[File:55 (Hu) Otszogletu zold tabla.svg|25px]] runs from Szeged to [[B\u00e1tasz\u00e9k]], via [[M\u00f3rahalom]].\n*[[File:451 (Hu) Otszogletu zold tabla.svg|25px]] runs from [[Kiskunf\u00e9legyh\u00e1za]] to Szentes, via [[Csongr\u00e1d]].\n*[[File:502 (Hu) Otszogletu zold tabla.svg|25px]] ''western bypass of Szeged.''\n\n== Politics ==\n{{Main article|Csongr\u00e1d County Assembly}}\nThe Csongr\u00e1d County Council, elected at the [[2019 Hungarian local elections|2019 local government elections]], is made up of 20 counselors<ref>{{cite web|title=Megyei k\u00f6zgy\u0171l\u00e9s tagjai 2019-2024 (Csongr\u00e1d megye)|url=https://www.valasztas.hu/megye-adatlap_onk2019?_onknavigacio_WAR_nvinvrportlet_formDate=32503680000000&p_p_id=onknavigacio_WAR_nvinvrportlet&p_p_lifecycle=1&p_p_state=normal&p